(82, '042482', 1, 6533, 'R5X2502J2344E59963 / H2S3992J2338E05380', 'Battery Lost communication', 'We require your assistance to conduct a diagnostic test on a client\'s system.\r\n\r\nOur client experienced a power outage on the night of April 24th, during which there were no mains power disruptions. Our installer confirmed the next day that the system caused the interruption.\r\n\r\nThe system reported a \'BMS Communication Lost Error\' with the code \'H2S3992J2338E05380\' at 7:01:11 PM on April 24th.\r\n\r\nYesterday, our installer returned to install a changeover switch. However, upon activating the inverter and battery, the battery failed to engage, and the inverter remained in standby mode.\r\n\r\nThe system operated flawlessly for three months prior to this incident. Our installer assures that the installation was correct and has exhausted all troubleshooting options without success.\r\n\r\nTemporarily, the battery has been switched off until your team can perform a diagnostic test.\r\n\r\nOur installer has briefed the client on activating the battery once your team guides him through the necessary tests over the phone', 'high', 'resolved', 0, 0, 13, '2024-04-25 23:38:36', '2024-06-21 03:52:20'),
(83, '042483', 1, 6491, 'Smile5 INV + ALPHA_SMILE-BAT-13.3P', 'Backup Plug Missing', 'From Steph: \r\nYou went to the below customers house last year but you were unable to complete the UPS backup due to a missing part, Do you have the part to complete this or not?\r\n\r\n\r\nIf not, What is the part? We are needing this completed in the next couple of weeks so if you could let me know asap and I can organise a part if needed and When would you like to go back?', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 13, '2024-04-26 00:39:56', '2024-06-21 03:52:00'),
(84, '042484', 1, 5967, 'AL7002223040397', 'System Performance', 'I\'m hoping you can make a bit of sense out of the attached PDF file\r\nI have put together. I been monitoring the Battery system since you\r\ngot it up and running. You set the original discharge times for one\r\nhour twice a day between 6.00am. and 7.00 am  of a morning and\r\n1800hrs and 1900hrs of an evening. I have experimented with \r\nchanging the discharge times from the one hour through to two\r\nand three hours with strange results. I will let you study it for a \r\nwhile and maybe you can explain it in simple terms for me later on.\r\nDue to the anomalies in the discharging I am going to monitor it\r\nof an evening over the week to ten days as it is set  for two hours\r\ndischarge between 5.30am. and 7.30am. of a morning and 1700hrs\r\nto 1900hrs of an evening and I will be in touch later next week.', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 13, '2024-04-26 01:35:14', '2025-05-28 08:56:27'),
