(106, '0524106', 1, 1536, NULL, 'Riso Low', 'In June 2011 Solarlink supplied to us a 2.5 kW PV system, which was installed by ADIWA Electrical services. A few days ago I noticed that the system was down with a \'Riso Low\' notice on the inverter display. I restarted the inverter but no change, i.e. the system would not initialize. I did some research which suggested I inspect the panels for any yellowing/browning around the panel cells. What I found was that at least one cell has a very brown \'framing\' and a whole lot of cells show yellowing. \r\nCould you please send out a technician to make an expert inspection and necessary measurements and subsequently let me know what my next\r\nsteps are? \r\nI have read the terms of the warranty provided by Solarlink and I believe that I am eligible for this warranty agreement to be honoured.', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-05-16 02:38:59', '2025-05-28 08:35:13'),
