(118, '0524118', 1, 6443, 'A1AU10051190072', 'Battery Issues', 'I have tried to ring a couple of times about our solar battery performance.  Our elec account has hardly changed from pre solar installation to now.  I am wondering if something has to be checked or \"restarted\" to fire up our battery.  I spoke to someone about 6 weeks ago and tried to log into battery data log ?  No progress.\r\nThe battery screen does not come up much at all.  I press it many times in various places and it does rarely operate.\r\nThe power went off about a month ago and the battery did not carry on to supply our system.\r\nDoes this need some extra \"service\" or connection to take over when the mains goes off ?\r\nCould the batteries be \"out of date\". ?  Both batteries had a sticker on the box \"must energize by 01 July 2023\", with manufacture date of 2021-06-15.\r\nThe system was fitted 4.12.23 and switched on 13.12.23  This is past the energise date.\r\nI am left wondering what may be at fault ?', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-05-24 01:00:31', '2024-09-06 09:51:51'),
