(153, '0624153', 1, 7356, NULL, 'Production Query', 'Client: Since having my solar panels connected, I have not noticed a huge reduction in my power bills, the reduction for Jan & Feb was approx. 40%, March was 20%, April was 18% and now my May usage is 4% more than last year, and also a jump of 374kw in 1 month.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nI have had a Power Pal Electricity Usage monitor installed today, and I checked them both at the same time, the Solis App said I was generating power and supplying 2.868kw to the grid, the Powerpal App noted I was using 6.1kw.\r\n\r\nThe Solis app also noted the load was .992kw.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nI have attached the screen shots of the 2 Apps for your information, and also a spreadsheet comparing power consumption from last year compared to this year.\r\n\r\nIs there a way that I can check if the solar panel inverter is working correctly?', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-06-25 22:51:08', '2024-08-01 03:00:48'),
