(155, '0624155', 1, 7591, 'P0CG8020262D061', 'System Issues', 'Since the system came online yesterday, it\'s only registering/showing generation to go straight into the grid, even though we have load in the house. It\'s registering load from the house as nil and pushing all generation to the grid. I\'m not sure if this is a config issue/display issue or something else?', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-06-27 01:54:35', '2024-07-09 00:34:11'),
(156, '0624156', 1, 7592, 'ALA001021090534', 'System Issues', 'Inspector was in today and I note the invoice has come through, so I will start getting that paid as per arrangement starting next week.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe inspector also agreed with me that the system should not be using any grid when batteries have plenty in them, and could not understand this morning when at times even with solar working, batteries at near 50%, the app still showed large fluctuations from the grid (it went from a few watts to many kilowatts) and has taken images of the app to get someone to look into it.\r\n\r\n\r\nYour tech mob tried to say it was normal when it adjusts for loads in the usage, BUT when no solar is being produced (ie at night, etc) there is no grid use at all regardless of load variations, it is only when solar is producing (or supposed to be as he could not also work out with sunny conditions, the solar went from producing several kilowatts to zero for a few minutes then back up to normal – something I told the techs about but they dismiss as they say no faults until it shows nothing for an hour or more…. Bit late then !!)\r\n \r\n\r\nWe now seem to be consuming around 2kw per day from the grid, regardless of battery capacity or solar production (as shown on our app and in the electricity providers usage in our account online), this is something that the inspector also said should not happen as we should be 100% solar/battery unless the batteries fall below the “Discharge cut off SOC” which is currently set 10%.\r\n\r\nCan you get someone to look into this please, rather than like the techs and just brush it off, as we have spent a lot with your company and would expect good follow up service. I agree with the inspector, that unless the battery drops below the SOC of 10%, we should not consume any grid power (especially since we never have large loads over 5kw.).', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-06-27 05:10:07', '2024-11-13 11:19:59'),
