(172, '0724172', 1, 7594, 'ALD001122121460 -	ALD001122120293', 'Battery Issues', 'Client reported an issue with the system.\r\n1. On 3-4 occassions the batteries have switched off and gone into fault mode (stragely at about 1730hrs each time).  There are no tripped switches / fuses on the main fuse board so I am not sure what is happening there.  This was not an issues prior to the installation (when we had a single Alpha battery). <br>  . The batteries are not charging from the generator.  When the generator runs, the batteries / inverters only draw enough power from the generator to cover the power usage in the house - they do not charge the batteries at all.  Prior to the new installation, the old battery / inverter would charge when the generator was running.\r\nThe main difference from a user perspective is that the Alpha App shows the batteries as running in grid mode and a grid reading can be seen on the app.  Prior to this installation, the Alpha app did not show a grid reading, the batteries simply charged at a higher rate and the grid reading remained at zero.  I am not a electrician but this leads me to believe the new wiring is slightly different - perhaps the generator is connected to the \'grid connection\' rather than a \'battery / generator connection\'? It certainly used to work as expected prior to the installation, and now it is not.\r\nThe main issue this causes is during overcast conditions - last week we had to run the generator all day to cover to the usage of the house in order to allow the solar to charge the batteries at a very low rate due to the cloud coverage.  This is not ideal or sustainable.', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-07-22 00:41:48', '2024-08-19 14:40:15'),
