(188, '0824188', 1, 5966, 'A2210300841', 'Battery Discharge Concern', 'I would like to ask about the battery that is part of my installation. I\'ve noticed a huge drop in the amount of time it takes to go from 100% to essentially empty (5% is where it cuts off).\r\nAt around this time last year, on those days the battery would manage to reach 100%, it would take from around 6pm to anywhere between 2am and 9am, with 6am being most common.\r\nNow, a 100% charge lasts maybe 3 hours. I don\'t believe my power usage has gone up that much, and this seems a little excessive for battery degredation. Is it possible there is a configuration or firmware issue? Or some other repairable fault?', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-08-06 04:39:46', '2024-10-21 12:15:20'),
(189, '0824189', 1, 6251, 'AL7011022090122', 'Production Query', 'We’ve had a Solar Link 6.6 kW Battery/Solar system for will over 12 months now and from date of installation we have been reviewing performance statistics from the AlphaESS monitoring web site. We understand the Alpha ESS monitoring system daily reports are generated from our digital power meter integrated in with our system. This daily report is quite extensive displaying information about our power usage, consumption etc.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nFor billing period as listed we have collated daily Grid Consumption and daily Feed In amounts in kWh’s from the solar monitoring system. The monitoring system differs substantially to our energy suppliers Billing kWh amounts for the SAME period.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSuppliers monitoring system lists   --- Total Usage (Grid consumption) 261.62 kWh, Total Solar Generation (Feed In) 49.5 kWh for 7th July 2024 to 3rd August 2024.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nWhy is there such a discrepancy with power company billing amounts to power monitoring software indicated amounts?', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-08-07 09:50:39', '2025-05-20 09:57:48'),
