(215, '0824215', 1, 7604, 'H2S2502J2345E06559', 'Back up circuit dropped out again', 'We had another 30 second drop out of the backup circuits again (at  8:09 PM Friday 23rd Aug)\r\n\r\nBasically the lighting and Fridge circuits dropped out for about 30 seconds and then automatically re-connected. I did not need to intervene in any way. The rest of the circuits did not loose power and there were no circuit breaker trips. \r\n\r\nOf course, these are the very circuits that should never drop out due to the UPS so something is amiss and it seems to be random. It seems not to be recorded anywhere. \r\n\r\nSo that his now 3 times:-\r\n9/8-7pm ; 12/8-11:23am and 23/8 8:09 pm.\r\n\r\nIs it possible that the protected circuits can be turned off by the inverter? (A glitch or something.)', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-08-28 09:27:06', '2024-10-21 13:36:59'),
(216, '0924216', 1, 6308, NULL, 'Solis Inverter Isn\'t Showing Any Sign Of Life', 'A new one for Monday morning. I lost hot water for the last 24H and on checking the setup the battery looks all good but the Solis inverter isn’t showing any sign of life at all. All switchboard CCT breakers are on and the battery app seems to show normal/good performance. The set up pre battery was that the hot water was fed by the solar inverter via a timer.', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2024-09-02 09:22:17', '2024-09-06 11:03:05'),
