(352, '0225352', 1, 7645, '001XOKD180054B / 001XOLP050075B', 'Battery Charing Issue', 'Newly installed RedX 2 x 5kwH system, turned on yesterday by ESV inspector. Not sure it\'s functioning correctly, when solar is working one battery charges to 100% then discharges into the other battery until down to 10%, then this repeats back the other way. And again. Plus when no solar input it doesn\'t appear house is running from the batteries, they are both \'idle\' and \'Passby\' and grid is inputting. Are they wired correctly? Thanks', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2025-02-04 11:23:05', '2025-05-16 10:55:25'),
(354, '0225353', 1, 6028, NULL, 'Black Out protection Issue', 'When the power went off at the weekend I switched the manual Black Out protection switch as  explained when installed, but no power from the battery went to the house.\r\n\r\nThis is the first time I have used the Black out Protection since you installed the product in October 2022.\r\n\r\nCould you please call and rectify the problem.', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2025-02-05 09:52:54', '2025-03-05 13:15:28'),
(355, '0225355', 1, 7646, 'ALD011123120001', 'System Query', 'Matt from G&J Appliance and Electrical came and installed the batteries on Wednesday Feb 5, however there\'s an issue with the way things have been wired. \r\n\r\nThe batteries (instead of the grid) seem to be supplying all the high wattage appliances (stove, hot water heater, oven and heat pump), in addition to the rest of the house. It\'s quite evident when observing on the app. \r\n\r\nMatt did state he was going to omit those appliances to keep the batteries from overdoing their output (5Kw). We\'ve had to tiptoe around using appliances simultaneously to avoid short circuiting the batteries.\r\n\r\nI\'ve called  and talked to Belinda from G&J Appliance and Electrical, and she was unsure when Matt could come back to fix things. I\'m hoping early next week. \r\n\r\nI\'m sure you won\'t mind if I pay the invoice once these issues are resolved.', 'low', 'resolved', 0, 0, 2, '2025-02-10 11:28:55', '2025-02-26 11:14:01'),
